==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Supersession
<hw>Su`per*ses"sion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. OF.
<ets>supersession</ets>. See <er>Supersede</er>.]</ety> <def>The act of
superseding, or the state of being superseded; supersedure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The general law of diminishing return from land would have
undergone, to that extent, a temporary <qex>supersession</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>J. S. Mill.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

